{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6da3c097-dc15-46b9-ad7b-d9a91485e05b","content":"Yes, both APIs are correct and available in .NET MAUI on .NET 10. Just make sure you're using the **MAUI namespace**, not the old Xamarin.Forms one:\n\n```xml\nxmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n```\n\nThen on your `ContentPage`:\n```xml\nios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"\n```\nThis insets the page content to avoid the notch/Dynamic Island and home indicator.\n\nFor a background image that should extend edge-to-edge behind the notch, use `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on the containing layout:\n```xml\n<Grid IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\">\n    <Image Source=\"background.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n</Grid>\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `UseSafeArea` is an **iOS platform-specific** — it only affects iOS; Android handles system bars differently (use `android:WindowSoftInputModeAdjust` or edge-to-edge APIs).\n- `IgnoreSafeArea` lets individual views break out of the safe area even when the page respects it — perfect for full-bleed backgrounds.\n- Both are stable APIs carried from early .NET MAUI into .NET 10.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a94130ac-6106-430a-b0ea-84d7cd4e42b3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repo doesn't have relevant content about safe area APIs. Let me answer based on my knowledge of .NET MAUI.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the safe area handling has changed from what it was in Xamarin.Forms:\n\n1. **`ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`** - This was the Xamarin.Forms approach using the `Xamarin.Forms.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific` namespace. In .NET MAUI, this still exists but the namespace changed. The platform-specific API is `Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific.Page.UseSafeArea`. So the XAML usage would be similar but with the updated namespace.\n\n\n2. **`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"`** - .NET MAUI introduced an `IgnoreSafeArea` property on views that lets specific views extend beyond the safe area, which is useful for background images or full-screen content. The `Page.UseSafeArea` property itself has been available since Xamarin.Forms and continues to work in .NET MAUI, telling the page to respect safe area insets on iOS.\n\nFor the platform-specific namespace in .NET MAUI, I need to use the correct assembly reference for iOS-specific APIs. The user's approach is generally sound, but they should verify they're using the current .NET MAUI namespace rather than the older Xamarin.Forms one. Both `UseSafeArea` and `IgnoreSafeArea` have been part of .NET MAUI since its early versions and should remain valid in .NET 10.","outputTokens":873,"requestId":"110F:3AF65D:CABE9A:ED1AA1:69FE895A"},"id":"b9640117-fe21-4a78-a6d0-656da9426d87","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:10:03.636Z","parentId":"c6cd71df-85bc-461a-9d55-3a23696b2602"}
